Class CertificateEncryptionPermissions

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum
      com.adobe.livecycle.encryption.client.CertificateEncryptionPermissions
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable
public final class CertificateEncryptionPermissions
extends java.lang.Enum

Represents enumeration values that correspond to permissions granted to a PDF document that is encrypted with a certificate.

See Also:

Field Detail

PKI_ALL_PERM

public static final CertificateEncryptionPermissions PKI_ALL_PERM
Represents all permissions.

PKI_EDIT_ADD

public static final CertificateEncryptionPermissions PKI_EDIT_ADD
Represents the permission that enables users to add form data. When you set this permission, you can perform the following tasks in Acrobat: add comments, fill in form fields, and digitally sign the document.

PKI_EDIT_COPY

public static final CertificateEncryptionPermissions PKI_EDIT_COPY
Represents the permission that enables users to copy form data.

PKI_EDIT_ASSEMBLE

public static final CertificateEncryptionPermissions PKI_EDIT_ASSEMBLE
Represents the permission that enables users to assemble PDF documents.

PKI_EDIT_EXTRACT

public static final CertificateEncryptionPermissions PKI_EDIT_EXTRACT
Represents the permission that enables users to extract data from forms.

PKI_EDIT_FORM_FILL

public static final CertificateEncryptionPermissions PKI_EDIT_FORM_FILL
Represents the permission that enables users to fill in forms. When you set this permission, you can perform the following tasks in Acrobat: fill in form fields, digitally sign the document, and create template pages.

PKI_EDIT_MODIFY

public static final CertificateEncryptionPermissions PKI_EDIT_MODIFY
Represents the permission that enables the users to edit the PDF document.

PKI_PRINT_HIGH

public static final CertificateEncryptionPermissions PKI_PRINT_HIGH
Allows high-resolution printing of documents. In order to set high-resolution printing, you must set both PKI_PRINT_HIGH and PKI_PRINT_LOW values.

PKI_PRINT_LOW

public static final CertificateEncryptionPermissions PKI_PRINT_LOW
Allows low-resolution printing of documents.
